did.head: DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY
did.physdesc: Printed Materials, Correspondence, Research Materials, Microfilm, Photographs
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: Includes correspondence, book reviews, subject files, and course material relating to his study of William Wordsworth and his career at Cornell. Also, correspondence between Jared Curtis, Coordinating Editor, and Stephen M. Parrish concerning The Cornell Wordsworth series and The Cornell Yeats series, as well as correspondence from others involved in those editing projects.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Includes correspondence, book reviews, subject files, and course material relating to his study of William Wordsworth and his career at Cornell.

Also, correspondence between Jared Curtis, Coordinating Editor, and Stephen M. Parrish concerning The Cornell Wordsworth series and The Cornell Yeats series, as well as correspondence from others involved in those editing projects.
Photographs by James Butler of an event celebrating the completion of the Wordsworth series held at Kendal at Ithaca on March 29, 2008.

Correspondence with Sally Bushell relating to The Excursion,1999-2002 and Mark L. Reed with Parrish, and letters between other editors and scholars relating to the series. Includes additional correspondence between Reed and Curtis, James Averill, Stephen Gill, Carl Ketcham, and Robert Osborn.

Cassette tapes of the Wordsworth Summer Conferences, 1991: Jonathan Wordsworth on Wordsworthian Comedy and 1998: Stephen Parrish on The Earliest Wordsworth; "Richard Wordsworth Reads the Poetry," and Jonathan Wordsworth/Studs Terkel talk.

Correspondence, grant proposals, reviews, and other files from Ann Saddlemyer, one of the general editors, relating to The Cornell Yeats series. Includes 17 CDs of interim stages of editions from Jared Curtis.

descgrp.head: INFORMATION FOR USERS
descgrp.p: CD-1594 through CD-1610 contains manuscript materials, including transcriptions and photographic reproductions of interim stages of editions from Jared Curtis - Cornell Yeats series
